body: @xkszltl : Can you paste your build cmd here. I would like to see which build options you have enabled.

@RyanUnderhill 
can you take a look at this?
Seems like if you enable both DNNL and TENSORRT, even though you are building a DNNL target it ends up including 
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/core/providers/shared_library/provider_interfaces.h#L8  ,which tries to include cuda_runtime.h

@RyanUnderhill @jywu-msft I face the same bug in 1.7.0 as well. Would there be a workaround for this?
Ubuntu 20.04
CUDA 11.2|
CUDNN 8.1
```
In file included from /workspace/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/shared_library/provider_api.h:149,
                 from /workspace/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/openvino/backend_manager.cc:4:
/workspace/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/shared_library/provider_interfaces.h:8:10: fatal error: cuda_runtime.h: No such file or directory
    8 | #include <cuda_runtime.h>
      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
```

PS: Build command can be found here: https://github.com/triton-inference-server/onnxruntime_backend/blob/main/tools/gen_ort_dockerfile.py#L160-L161
@weixingzhang Do you know why those lines were added? It was part of this changelist you committed: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/commit/299ace0759192557e97e14d03c08f0334c84e9d5
Nvidia Triton is blocked from consuming ORT ver 1.7.1 due to this issue.

How's the issue on this?
We've been blocked on this for quite a while and seems the issue is still there in 1.7.2.
What will be the ETA for 1.7.3?
